Facebook removed the trailer for upcoming ABC TV show 8MMM Aboriginal Radio because it contained 'potentially offensive nudity' The clip shows two elderly women painted in ochre dancing in a traditional ceremony . 
  The show's co-creator Rachel Clements called Facebook's decision 'silly and disrespectful to the women who were dancing for us' The video was removed after three days on Sunday . 
  Fans have called the decision 'outrageous' and 'ridiculous'